The biggest energy-related news out of China this week has involved transport ‚Äì the mega-traffic jam in Inner Mongolia, leading to Beijing.  After more than ten days, extra police did manage to redirect traffic and clear the jam.  While this story has played mainly as a global human interest story with many suggesting visions of futuristic nightmares, the actual causes, well outlined in <a href="http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052748704540904575451791942262532.html">Shai Oster‚Äôs Wall Street Journal blog</a> are far more complex than just the number of vehicles on the road.
